<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. Santos &amp; Buril" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ipomoea maranhensis" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maranhensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Ipomoea maranhensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from two disjunct populations between the municipality of Mirador, in the Mirador State Park (area of 4370 km2) and the municipality of Carolina, in the National Park Chapada das Mesas (CMNP, area of 1600 km2) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution map of Ipomoea maranhensis." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.151.49833.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/422484" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">4</figureCitation>
). In both areas this species grows on quartzite soils associated with Cerrado vegetation at 186-345 m elevation, average temperature of 26 °C and annual precipitation between 1250-1500 mm (
<bibRefCitation author="Alcantara, EH" journalOrPublisher="Caminhos de Geografia" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="97 - 113" publicationUrl="http://files.nea.webnode.com/200000006-3cfc83df67/artigo07_vol11_Itapecuru.pdf" refId="B1" refString="Alcantara, EH, 2004. Caracterizacao da bacia hidrografica do rio Itapecuru, Maranhao Brasil. Caminhos de Geografia 7 (11): 97 - 113, http://files.nea.webnode.com/200000006-3cfc83df67/artigo07_vol11_Itapecuru.pdf" title="Caracterizacao da bacia hidrografica do rio Itapecuru, Maranhao Brasil." url="http://files.nea.webnode.com/200000006-3cfc83df67/artigo07_vol11_Itapecuru.pdf" volume="7" year="2004">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Alcântara">Alcantara</normalizedToken>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="IBAMA" journalOrPublisher="Spring Lake Publishing, Spring Lake, Utah" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" publicationUrl="https://www.ibama.gov.br/phocadownload/prevfogo/planos_operativos/plano_operativoparna_da_chapada_das_mesas.pdf" refId="B12" refString="IBAMA, 2013. Plano Operativo De Prevencao e Combate aos Incendios Florestais do Parque Nacional da Chapada das Mesas. Ministerio do Meio Ambiente, Carolina. https://www.ibama.gov.br/phocadownload/prevfogo/planos_operativos/plano_operativoparna_da_chapada_das_mesas.pdf" title="Plano Operativo De Prevencao e Combate aos Incendios Florestais do Parque Nacional da Chapada das Mesas. Ministerio do Meio Ambiente, Carolina." url="https://www.ibama.gov.br/phocadownload/prevfogo/planos_operativos/plano_operativoparna_da_chapada_das_mesas.pdf" year="2013">IBAMA 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The occurrence of this new species in the National Park Chapada das Mesas and in the Mirador State Park emphasizes the importance of these protected areas for the preservation of this taxon in the Cerrado domain.
</paragraph>
